Step 1: Setup Environment

You need 2 systems:

Option A (Recommended for you)
Control Node → Your system (Ubuntu / WSL / VM)
Target Node → EC2 instance (AWS) OR another VM
Step 2: Install Ansible (Control Node)

Open terminal:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible -y

Check installation:

ansible --version
Step 3: Setup Target Server

If using AWS EC2 (recommended for marks):

Launch Ubuntu EC2 instance
Allow port 22 (SSH) and port 80 (HTTP)

Connect:

ssh ubuntu@<your-ec2-ip>
Fix Step-by-Step (Do EXACTLY this)
Step 1: Locate Your .pem File

Find where your key is downloaded
Example:

Downloads → ansible-key.pem

Then go to that folder:

cd C:\Users\hp\Downloads

Check:

dir

You should see:

ansible-key.pem

Fix (Correct Command)

Use this instead:

icacls ansible-key.pem /grant:r "$env:USERNAME:R"
Full Correct Steps (Clean)

You are already in the correct folder:

cd C:\Users\hp\Downloads

Now run:

icacls ansible-key.pem /inheritance:r
