Step 1: Exit EC2 (Go back to Control Node)

Type:

exit

You should return to:

PS C:\Users\hp\Downloads>
Step 2: Make Sure You Are Using WSL (IMPORTANT)

Ansible does NOT run natively on Windows PowerShell
You must use:

Ubuntu (WSL) OR
Linux VM

Open WSL:

wsl
Step 3: Install Ansible (in WSL)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible -y

Check:

ansible --version
Step 4: Move Your Key File to WSL

Your key is here:

C:\Users\hp\Downloads\ansible-key.pem

In WSL:

cp /mnt/c/Users/hp/Downloads/ansible-key.pem ~/
chmod 400 ansible-key.pem
Step 5: Create Inventory File
nano hosts

Paste:

[webservers]
15.206.80.9 ansible_user=ubuntu ansible_ssh_private_key_file=~/ansible-key.pem

Save: CTRL + X → Y → ENTER

Step 6: Test Connection (VERY IMPORTANT)
ansible -i hosts webservers -m ping

Expected:

SUCCESS => pong
Step 7: Create Playbook
nano install_nginx.yml

Paste:

- name: Install Nginx Web Server
  hosts: webservers
  become: yes

  tasks:
    - name: Update apt repository
      apt:
        update_cache: yes

    - name: Install Nginx
      apt:
        name: nginx
        state: present

    - name: Start Nginx service
      service:
        name: nginx
        state: started
        enabled: yes
Step 8: Run Playbook
ansible-playbook -i hosts install_nginx.yml

You will see tasks like:

TASK [Install Nginx]
changed: [15.206.80.9]
Step 9: Verify Nginx

Open browser:

http://15.206.80.9

Step 10: Final Check via SSH
ssh -i ansible-key.pem ubuntu@15.206.80.9
sudo systemctl status nginx
